'''Floryshe''' ("To Flourish") is an English term from at least the mid 1300s used in the brief English sword text, MS 39564, c. mid-1400s, to refer to the brandishing of a weapon with large showy movements during practice or prior to play or fight. 

The term is currently used within The [[Association for Renaissance Martial Arts]] to mean an unstructured practice routine of guard transitions, cuts, thrusts, slices and parries with appropriate footwork.